1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
3 Article – Education
4 15–140.
5 (A) AN INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION:
6 (1) SHALL PROVIDE REASONABLE ACCOMMODATIONS TO A STUDENT
7 WITH SICKLE CELL DISEASE; AND
8 (2) MAY NOT DENY ACCESS TO FACILITIES OR SERVICES TO A
9 STUDENT BASED ON THE STUDENT’S DIAGNOSIS OF SICKLE CELL DISEASE.
10 (B) AN INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION SHALL ESTABLISH A
11 PROCEDURE THROUGH WHICH A PERSON MAY REPORT AN ALLEGED VIOLATION OF
12 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION.
13 (C) AN INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION SHALL PUBLICIZE IN A
14 MANNER THAT IS CLEAR AND ACCESSIBLE TO STUDENTS:
15 (1) THE REQUIREMENTS OF SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION; AND
16 (2) THE REPORTING PROCEDURE ESTABLISHED UNDER SUBSECTION
17 (B) OF THIS SECTION.
18 Article – Health – General
19 18–510.
20 (A) THE DEPARTMENT, IN CONSULTATION WITH SICKLE CELL DISEASE
21 TREATMENT PROVIDERS AND COMMUNITY–BASED ORGANIZATIONS, SHALL
22 DEVELOP AN EDUCATION AND AWARENESS CAMPAIGN FOR INSTITUTIONS OF
23 HIGHER EDUCATION IN THE STATE REGARDING STUDENTS WITH SICKLE CELL
24 DISEASE.
25 (B) THE PROGRAM DEVELOPED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION
26 SHALL:
27 (1) DESCRIBE CHALLENGES FACED BY YOUNG ADULTS LIVING WITH
28 SICKLE CELL DISEASE, WITH AN EMPHASIS ON CHALLENGES FACED DURING HEALTH
29 CRISES RELATED TO SICKLE CELL DISEASE; AND

