1 (2) PROVIDE INFORMATION ON ACCOMMODATIONS AND SUPPORT
2 THAT INSTITUTIONS OF HIGHER EDUCATION CAN PROVIDE TO STUDENTS WITH
3 SICKLE CELL DISEASE TO ENABLE THE STUDENTS TO SUCCEED ACADEMICALLY
4 WHILE MANAGING SICKLE CELL DISEASE.
5 18–511.
6 (A) THE DEPARTMENT, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE MARYLAND HIGHER
7 EDUCATION COMMISSION, SHALL DEVELOP UNIFORM PROCEDURES FOR
8 INSTITUTIONS OF HIGHER EDUCATION IN THE STATE TO FOLLOW IN ASSESSING,
9 SUPPORTING, AND TREATING STUDENTS WITH SICKLE CELL DISEASE.
10 (B) THE DEPARTMENT AND THE MARYLAND HIGHER EDUCATION
11 COMMISSION JOINTLY SHALL:
12 (1) BEGINNING DECEMBER 1, 2025, PROVIDE TECHNICAL
13 ASSISTANCE TO INSTITUTIONS OF HIGHER EDUCATION TO:
14 (I) IMPLEMENT THE PROCEDURES DEVELOPED UNDER THIS
15 SECTION; AND
16 (II) INSTRUCT PERSONNEL OF INSTITUTIONS OF HIGHER
17 EDUCATION REGARDING THE PROCEDURES DEVELOPED UNDER THIS SECTION; AND
18 (2) ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 1, 2025, DEVELOP A PROCESS TO
19 MONITOR THE IMPLEMENTATION OF THE PROCEDURES BY INSTITUTIONS OF
20 HIGHER EDUCATION.
21 18–512.
22 (A) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DEVELOP OR COMPILE MATERIALS TO
23 PROVIDE HEALTH PERSONNEL, FACULTY, AND ADMINISTRATIVE STAFF EMPLOYED
24 AT AN INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION IN THE STATE WITH A COMPREHENSIVE
25 EDUCATION ON SICKLE CELL DISEASE.
26 (B) THE MATERIALS DEVELOPED OR COMPILED UNDER THIS SECTION
27 SHALL FOCUS ON ENHANCING UNDERSTANDING OF SICKLE CELL DISEASE,
28 REDUCING STIGMAS, AND FOSTERING A SUPPORTIVE LEARNING ENVIRONMENT FOR
29 STUDENTS WITH SICKLE CELL DISEASE.

